### React Three Fiber Event Data Structure

Source: https://github.com/pmndrs/react-three-fiber/blob/master/docs/API/events.mdx

This details the structure of the event object passed to event handlers in React Three Fiber. It includes all original browser event data, three.js intersection data, and specific properties like the intersected object, unprojected point, and the ray used.

```jsx
({
  ...DomEvent                   // All the original event data
  ...Intersection                 // All of Three's intersection data - see note 2
  intersections: Intersection[]    // The first intersection of each intersected object
  object: Object3D              // The object that was actually hit
  eventObject: Object3D         // The object that registered the event
  unprojectedPoint: Vector3     // Camera-unprojected point
  ray: Ray                      // The ray that was used to strike the object
  camera: Camera                // The camera that was used in the raycaster
  sourceEvent: DomEvent         // A reference to the host event
  delta: number                 // Distance between mouse down and mouse up event in pixels
}) => ...
```

