### Pointer Events

Source: https://github.com/pmndrs/react-three-fiber/blob/master/docs/tutorials/how-it-works.mdx

Pointer events are transparently managed by Fiber, which initializes a raycaster for mouse picking upon startup. Any object assigned an onPointer prop is automatically included in the raycaster's check array, which is processed every frame. The ray's origin and direction are dynamically updated in response to mouse movement or window resizing. Furthermore, Fiber intelligently handles camera switching, ensuring that the raycaster consistently utilizes the currently active camera for accurate interaction detection.

